│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation happens because SLP merges lanes with different cast kinds (sext vs zext) into a single vectorized cast, effectively turning a zext into a sext │
│ for some lanes. That breaks nuw semantics on the subsequent add and produces poison. To fix, we should make SLP refuse to vectorize a group of CastInst when their opcodes  │
│ are not uniform. The section around getEntry uniqueness/opcode handling already computes UniqueOpcodes; we need to enforce that for CastInst groups, UniqueOpcodes.size()   │
│ must be 1. I'll patch SLPVectorizer.cpp to add a guard in the opcode handling path so mixed sext/zext groups are not vectorized and instead gathered as-is.                 │
