╭─ assistant [MainThread@620594] ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ THOUGHT: The miscompilation arises from vectorizing cast groups in the SLP vectorizer, particularly when mixing ZExt and SExt across lanes. As a conservative mitigation to │
│ prevent incorrect transformations, I will disable vectorization for cast nodes by changing the cast handling to create a NeedToGather entry instead of a vectorized one.    │
│ This avoids merging mixed cast kinds and prevents poison while keeping the rest of SLP intact.                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ sed -i '8389,8391s/newTreeEntry(VL, Bundle \/\*vectorized\*\/, S, UserTreeIdx,/newTreeEntry(VL, TreeEntry::NeedToGather, Bundle, S, UserTreeIdx,/'                          │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch                                                                                                             │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                         │
